The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Jaya suit on DMK boss

 Chennai, June 13: The Jayalalithaa government today filed a defamation case against DMK president M. Karunanidhi for alleging that the chief minister had sinister motives behind arresting Kanchi seer Jayendra Saraswati, reports our special correspondent. 

 The civil suit came up before the principal sessions judge, who posted it for hearing on June 20. 

 The seer, the main accused in the murder of temple manager Shankar Raman, was held on November 11.

 The state governments suit alleged that the DMK chiefs comments ? made at a news conference on November 22 ? sought to harm the chief ministers reputation. 




